00:10:23.415 --> 00:10:27.335 position:50% align:center
Huh? That is absolutely "re-fa."

00:10:27.419 --> 00:10:30.380 position:50% align:center
No, it was "do-fa," for sure.

00:10:30.463 --> 00:10:33.675 position:50% align:center
No. Really? You sound stupid.

00:10:33.758 --> 00:10:36.261 position:50% align:center
[IKETERU] Only stupid people
call people stupid.

00:10:36.344 --> 00:10:37.220 position:50% align:center
Are you nuts?

00:10:37.303 --> 00:10:39.139 position:50% align:center
[IKETERU]
Am I n--? Heh...

00:10:39.222 --> 00:10:40.348 position:50% align:center
You ding-dong.

00:10:40.432 --> 00:10:41.683 position:50% align:center
[IKETERU]
Dong.

00:10:41.766 --> 00:10:45.228 position:50% align:center
[MABUI] I can't share a
space with you right now.

00:10:45.311 --> 00:10:46.563 position:50% align:center
What?

00:10:46.646 --> 00:10:48.314 position:50% align:center
Looks like it's just
gonna be the two of us

00:10:48.398 --> 00:10:49.983 position:50% align:center
for a while, Sayuri.

00:10:50.066 --> 00:10:51.818 position:50% align:center
Go be a dingusaurus
somewhere else

00:10:51.901 --> 00:10:54.529 position:50% align:center
and you can come back
when you're done.

00:10:54.612 --> 00:10:56.740 position:50% align:center
[IKETERU]
Wait, why?

00:10:56.823 --> 00:10:58.324 position:50% align:center
[MABUI]
'Cause it's "re-fa."

00:10:58.408 --> 00:11:00.535 position:50% align:center
[IKETERU]
That is clearly "do-fa."

00:11:00.618 --> 00:11:02.412 position:50% align:center
[MABUI]
Get out.

00:11:02.495 --> 00:11:04.456 position:50% align:center
[IKETERU] I got into a pretty
big fight with my sister

00:11:04.539 --> 00:11:06.750 position:50% align:center
and she kicked me out.

00:11:06.833 --> 00:11:10.837 position:50% align:center
[sighs] I don't know where
I'm supposed to go.

00:11:13.214 --> 00:11:14.799 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
So, a cat video.

00:11:14.883 --> 00:11:15.842 position:50% align:center
[UTANO]
Why does that matter?

00:11:15.925 --> 00:11:17.093 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Are you children?

00:11:17.177 --> 00:11:18.470 position:50% align:center
[UTANO]
How's that even a fight?

00:11:18.553 --> 00:11:19.179 position:50% align:center
Hold on.

00:11:19.262 --> 00:11:20.513 position:50% align:center
Guys, one at a time.

00:11:20.597 --> 00:11:24.142 position:50% align:center
That's more questions than
he can process at once.

00:11:24.225 --> 00:11:26.019 position:50% align:center
[UTANO]
Hmm...

00:11:26.102 --> 00:11:29.481 position:50% align:center
Though Mabui can get intense
over that kinda thing.

00:11:29.564 --> 00:11:32.317 position:50% align:center
Uh! That's it! I had forgotten.

00:11:32.400 --> 00:11:34.694 position:50% align:center
You were friends with
Mabui, weren't you?

00:11:34.778 --> 00:11:38.448 position:50% align:center
Oh. Right. Yeah. We've been
friends since college.

00:11:38.531 --> 00:11:40.575 position:50% align:center
You can have my sister
for the night!

00:11:40.658 --> 00:11:42.160 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI]
See? You shorted him out.

00:11:42.243 --> 00:11:43.370 position:50% align:center
[IKETERU]
Please help me!

00:11:43.453 --> 00:11:44.746 position:50% align:center
Call her up and
ask her if you two

00:11:44.829 --> 00:11:46.247 position:50% align:center
can catch up over
dinner or something

00:11:46.331 --> 00:11:48.541 position:50% align:center
and get her to sleep
on your couch!

00:11:48.625 --> 00:11:50.126 position:50% align:center
Right. I get the idea.

00:11:50.210 --> 00:11:53.129 position:50% align:center
But I live with my boyfriend,
so that's not gonna work.

00:11:53.213 --> 00:11:56.383 position:50% align:center
Uh. I would be happy to
look after your boyfriend!

00:11:56.466 --> 00:11:57.300 position:50% align:center
[UTANO]
Okay, slow down.

00:11:57.384 --> 00:11:58.551 position:50% align:center
We can do a swap!

00:11:58.635 --> 00:12:00.637 position:50% align:center
[UTANO] We're definitely
losing the plot, here.

00:12:00.720 --> 00:12:01.930 position:50% align:center
[IKETERU]
Uh, then,

00:12:02.013 --> 00:12:03.765 position:50% align:center
you can send your boyfriend
over to my place

00:12:03.848 --> 00:12:05.850 position:50% align:center
and I'll go hang out
at Kumatani's place!

00:12:05.934 --> 00:12:07.227 position:50% align:center
[UTANO]
You're making it worse.

00:12:07.310 --> 00:12:08.478 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI]
I would be okay with that.

00:12:08.561 --> 00:12:10.563 position:50% align:center
[UTANO]
Don't encourage him.

00:12:10.647 --> 00:12:11.731 position:50% align:center
Okay, lemme think.

00:12:11.815 --> 00:12:14.234 position:50% align:center
No, it's fine. I'll kick
my boyfriend out.

00:12:14.317 --> 00:12:15.860 position:50% align:center
Sucks to be him, I guess.

00:12:15.944 --> 00:12:17.904 position:50% align:center
And then we'll meet up
at Uramichi's place.

00:12:17.987 --> 00:12:19.364 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
What?

00:12:20.323 --> 00:12:23.535 position:50% align:center
Kids are coming in for
taping number two, everybody!

00:12:23.618 --> 00:12:25.995 position:50% align:center
Got it! Let's do this.

00:12:26.079 --> 00:12:27.622 position:50% align:center
[IKETERU]
Right.

00:12:27.706 --> 00:12:31.459 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI] Good to see
everyone! <i>Konnichiwa</i> !

00:12:31.543 --> 00:12:34.170 position:50% align:center
I'm Uramichi,
your gymnast Oniisan!

00:12:34.254 --> 00:12:37.132 position:50% align:center
I hope you're all ready to have
lots of fun with your big bro!

00:12:37.215 --> 00:12:41.219 position:50% align:center
[BOY G, GIRL F crying]

00:12:41.302 --> 00:12:43.430 position:50% align:center
Hey, guys! What's wrong?

00:12:43.513 --> 00:12:46.016 position:50% align:center
It seems like you two
aren't getting along.

00:12:46.099 --> 00:12:48.059 position:50% align:center
She just hit me for no reason!

00:12:48.143 --> 00:12:51.479 position:50% align:center
Quit lying, you butt!
You were stepping on my foot!

00:12:51.563 --> 00:12:52.772 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
Well, it sounds like both of you

00:12:52.856 --> 00:12:54.399 position:50% align:center
did something you
shouldn't have,

00:12:54.482 --> 00:12:56.735 position:50% align:center
so why don't you
apologize to each other?

00:12:56.818 --> 00:12:57.444 position:50% align:center
No!

00:12:57.527 --> 00:12:59.779 position:50% align:center
It wasn't my fault!

00:12:59.863 --> 00:13:01.448 position:50% align:center
Do you wanna know a secret?

00:13:01.531 --> 00:13:02.949 position:50% align:center
Grown-ups like me
get through the day

00:13:03.033 --> 00:13:05.869 position:50% align:center
thanks to a magic force
called "responsibility."

00:13:05.952 --> 00:13:07.203 position:50% align:center
It's a curse.

00:13:07.287 --> 00:13:10.081 position:50% align:center
See, kids, we have
a duty to say sorry.

00:13:10.165 --> 00:13:11.541 position:50% align:center
Whether it's our fault or not,

00:13:11.624 --> 00:13:14.544 position:50% align:center
responsibility makes
it our problem.

00:13:16.713 --> 00:13:18.882 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI] But still,
I don't think of apologizing

00:13:18.965 --> 00:13:20.425 position:50% align:center
as abandoning your pride.

00:13:20.508 --> 00:13:22.260 position:50% align:center
Sometimes it's just
the easiest way

00:13:22.344 --> 00:13:24.346 position:50% align:center
to keep things smooth
between people.

00:13:24.429 --> 00:13:26.723 position:50% align:center
Walking away mad is
like hitting snooze.

00:13:26.806 --> 00:13:28.975 position:50% align:center
You'll still have to
face facts eventually,

00:13:29.059 --> 00:13:30.560 position:50% align:center
and if you keep putting it off,

00:13:30.643 --> 00:13:33.980 position:50% align:center
you're only going to make your
own life tougher in the end.

00:13:34.064 --> 00:13:36.358 position:50% align:center
Sometimes, doing
the hard thing early

00:13:36.441 --> 00:13:39.069 position:50% align:center
makes things easier later on.

00:13:40.445 --> 00:13:43.823 position:50% align:center
Um, I'm sorry about
when I hit you earlier.

00:13:43.907 --> 00:13:47.369 position:50% align:center
Me, too. Sorry for
stepping on your foot.

00:13:47.452 --> 00:13:52.999 position:50% align:center
Yay! You both did that
perfectly! Great job!

00:13:53.083 --> 00:13:55.293 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA] I'm pretty positive
Uramichi's worn a hole

00:13:55.377 --> 00:13:57.379 position:50% align:center
through his snooze button.

00:14:05.303 --> 00:14:08.890 position:50% align:center
So... I'm back.

00:14:11.935 --> 00:14:14.854 position:50% align:center
Um. Sorry.

00:14:14.938 --> 00:14:17.982 position:50% align:center
That fight. Um... I...

00:14:19.526 --> 00:14:23.947 position:50% align:center
What fight? We fought?

00:14:24.030 --> 00:14:25.907 position:50% align:center
What was it about?

00:14:30.578 --> 00:14:33.081 position:50% align:center
[IKETERU]
What was it about?

00:14:34.457 --> 00:14:37.877 position:50% align:center
[meows]

00:14:40.463 --> 00:14:43.216 position:50% align:center
[AMON]
It's crap.

00:14:43.299 --> 00:14:46.803 position:50% align:center
All these new segments I'm
coming up with are total crap.

00:14:46.886 --> 00:14:49.055 position:50% align:center
Man, it's a Sunday special,

00:14:49.139 --> 00:14:50.640 position:50% align:center
but I can't think
of anything special

00:14:50.724 --> 00:14:52.726 position:50% align:center
we can actually put in the show!

00:14:52.809 --> 00:14:54.352 position:50% align:center
So who the heck is this guy?

00:14:54.436 --> 00:14:56.563 position:50% align:center
You can't be serious.

00:14:56.646 --> 00:15:00.650 position:50% align:center
That's the other director, Amon.
He's been here the whole time.

00:15:00.734 --> 00:15:02.610 position:50% align:center
We need new. We need different.

00:15:02.694 --> 00:15:04.529 position:50% align:center
Was he like this the whole time?

00:15:04.612 --> 00:15:05.864 position:50% align:center
For real?

00:15:05.947 --> 00:15:08.450 position:50% align:center
[AMON]
All of you, I need help.

00:15:08.533 --> 00:15:11.411 position:50% align:center
Everyone tell me about
a dream you had recently.

00:15:11.494 --> 00:15:12.245 position:50% align:center
[IKETERU]
Like the fish?

00:15:12.328 --> 00:15:13.538 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI]
That's "bream."

00:15:13.621 --> 00:15:14.247 position:50% align:center
--[USAHARA] Azuki!
--[KUMATANI] That's a bean.

00:15:14.330 --> 00:15:15.457 position:50% align:center
I need a good story

00:15:15.540 --> 00:15:18.585 position:50% align:center
to get the wheels of my
imagination turning.

00:15:18.668 --> 00:15:19.878 position:50% align:center
You go first.

00:15:19.961 --> 00:15:21.254 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Huh? Who, me?

00:15:21.338 --> 00:15:24.341 position:50% align:center
Let's see. A dream, huh?
Oh! I had a dream where--

00:15:24.424 --> 00:15:26.509 position:50% align:center
[AMON]
Your dream is boring. Next!

00:15:26.593 --> 00:15:28.136 position:50% align:center
That's harsh.

00:15:29.763 --> 00:15:33.725 position:50% align:center
Heading home one night,
I suddenly felt a sensation,

00:15:33.808 --> 00:15:36.853 position:50% align:center
like some odd presence
was pursuing me.

00:15:40.857 --> 00:15:43.651 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI] I turned around
to look and saw nothing,

00:15:43.735 --> 00:15:45.070 position:50% align:center
but I could feel them.

00:15:45.153 --> 00:15:49.824 position:50% align:center
I could tell they were
following me. Dozens of them.

00:15:53.036 --> 00:15:56.539 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI] Still, I kept
walking, got home, took a bath,

00:15:56.623 --> 00:15:58.833 position:50% align:center
and went to sleep.

00:15:58.917 --> 00:16:02.253 position:50% align:center
Then, obviously,
I woke up the next morning.

00:16:02.337 --> 00:16:05.423 position:50% align:center
But I realized I might've been
waking up into another dream,

00:16:05.507 --> 00:16:07.634 position:50% align:center
and I'd have no way
of knowing if I was.

00:16:07.717 --> 00:16:10.261 position:50% align:center
None of us do. For all
I know, I never woke u--

00:16:10.345 --> 00:16:11.721 position:50% align:center
Thank you! Next dream!

00:16:11.805 --> 00:16:14.391 position:50% align:center
I had a really nice dream
where I played with my dog.

00:16:14.474 --> 00:16:16.184 position:50% align:center
Boy, it was fun!

00:16:16.267 --> 00:16:17.977 position:50% align:center
[AMON]
Next, please.

00:16:21.064 --> 00:16:26.319 position:50% align:center
I was at the bridal shop...
choosing my wedding dress.

00:16:26.403 --> 00:16:29.406 position:50% align:center
And for the reception, this
bold, autumn red number--

00:16:29.489 --> 00:16:31.157 position:50% align:center
[AMON]
Okay, next!

00:16:31.241 --> 00:16:35.036 position:50% align:center
Ah, crap. Welp, it's just you.

00:16:38.164 --> 00:16:41.960 position:50% align:center
I had a dream of a
world without <i>yakumi</i> .

00:16:42.043 --> 00:16:44.170 position:50% align:center
<i>Yakumi</i> ? I'm intrigued.

00:16:44.254 --> 00:16:47.048 position:50% align:center
Tell me of this
<i>yakumi</i> -less world.

00:16:47.132 --> 00:16:49.134 position:50% align:center
First, I went out to get sushi

00:16:49.217 --> 00:16:52.095 position:50% align:center
and the restaurant
didn't have any wasabi.

00:16:52.178 --> 00:16:54.180 position:50% align:center
So I settled on somen,

00:16:54.264 --> 00:16:56.766 position:50% align:center
but they didn't have
shiso or <i>myoga</i> there.

00:16:56.850 --> 00:16:59.060 position:50% align:center
I had to resort to
a beef bowl joint,

00:16:59.144 --> 00:17:02.856 position:50% align:center
but they didn't even have
scallions or pickled ginger.

00:17:04.899 --> 00:17:07.610 position:50% align:center
Then what? What did you do next?

00:17:07.694 --> 00:17:09.571 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
Life went on for a while,

00:17:09.654 --> 00:17:12.782 position:50% align:center
even without the signature
taste of Japanese cuisine.

00:17:12.866 --> 00:17:15.660 position:50% align:center
But with no garnishes, the
souls of the adults withered,

00:17:15.744 --> 00:17:17.787 position:50% align:center
and we became shambling husks.

00:17:17.871 --> 00:17:20.373 position:50% align:center
The children built
a flourishing new world,

00:17:20.457 --> 00:17:23.001 position:50% align:center
unburdened by the loss of
flavors they'd never known.

00:17:23.084 --> 00:17:26.296 position:50% align:center
[AMON]
Brilliant. It's brilliant!

00:17:26.379 --> 00:17:30.884 position:50% align:center
My imagination is on fire now!

00:17:30.967 --> 00:17:33.636 position:50% align:center
[IKETERU]
Ha! Boy, it was fun!

00:17:33.720 --> 00:17:38.725 position:50% align:center
[KIDS chattering]

00:17:42.062 --> 00:17:43.438 position:50% align:center
[KIDS]
Huh?

00:17:48.401 --> 00:17:51.446 position:50% align:center
♪ Like <i>shinobi</i> in the shadows,
we sit on your plate. ♪

00:17:51.529 --> 00:17:52.864 position:50% align:center
[BOY F]
What is this?

00:17:52.947 --> 00:17:54.282 position:50% align:center
♪ And if it's halfway decent,
we can make it great. ♪

00:17:54.366 --> 00:17:55.784 position:50% align:center
[GIRL I]
I have no idea!

00:17:55.867 --> 00:17:58.578 position:50% align:center
♪ Imparting flavor subtly,
the Yakumi Shinobi! ♪

00:17:58.661 --> 00:18:01.081 position:50% align:center
My name is Momiji
and I'm a <i>kunoichi</i> !

00:18:01.164 --> 00:18:03.708 position:50% align:center
One day, I was grating my
daikon when I nicked my finger

00:18:03.792 --> 00:18:05.210 position:50% align:center
and dyed it red
as autumn leaves,

00:18:05.293 --> 00:18:07.087 position:50% align:center
just like <i>momiji oroshi</i> !

00:18:07.170 --> 00:18:09.005 position:50% align:center
I'm Neginosuke the ninja,

00:18:09.089 --> 00:18:11.591 position:50% align:center
and I was in such a hurry to get
home from the grocery store

00:18:11.675 --> 00:18:12.842 position:50% align:center
and play with my dog

00:18:12.926 --> 00:18:14.928 position:50% align:center
that I totally forgot
to pick up the leeks!

00:18:15.011 --> 00:18:17.013 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI] Ever since that time
I bit into a raw ginger root

00:18:17.097 --> 00:18:18.348 position:50% align:center
when I was messed
up with a cold,

00:18:18.431 --> 00:18:20.975 position:50% align:center
the taste has kinda
bothered me, grr.

00:18:21.059 --> 00:18:23.144 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA] I saw a bird that
looked like a <i>myoga</i> bud,

00:18:23.228 --> 00:18:24.562 position:50% align:center
and I laughed so hippity hard

00:18:24.646 --> 00:18:27.107 position:50% align:center
that I made it my phone's
background, hop!

00:18:27.190 --> 00:18:30.110 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
Excellent work, <i>shinobi</i> .

00:18:30.193 --> 00:18:32.779 position:50% align:center
It is I, the god of shiso.

00:18:32.862 --> 00:18:34.864 position:50% align:center
Born from the resentment
of a shiso crop

00:18:34.948 --> 00:18:38.410 position:50% align:center
torn asunder by a typhoon.

00:18:38.493 --> 00:18:40.620 position:50% align:center
[KIDS]
Uh...

00:18:44.666 --> 00:18:48.169 position:50% align:center
[GIRL J] God of shiso, why are
you wearing a mesh tank top?

00:18:48.253 --> 00:18:51.256 position:50% align:center
There are some things that
even the gods may never know.

00:18:51.339 --> 00:18:54.467 position:50% align:center
And if I did allow myself to
think about what I'm wearing,

00:18:54.551 --> 00:18:57.512 position:50% align:center
I wouldn't be able to appear
in front of humans at all.

00:18:57.595 --> 00:18:59.472 position:50% align:center
Do you know why all
of the Yakumi Shinobi

00:18:59.556 --> 00:19:01.808 position:50% align:center
are trying so hard
not to look at you?

00:19:01.891 --> 00:19:03.435 position:50% align:center
I can only speculate,

00:19:03.518 --> 00:19:06.062 position:50% align:center
but every time anybody looked
directly at me in rehearsal,

00:19:06.146 --> 00:19:09.274 position:50% align:center
they would break character
and forget all their lines.

00:19:11.192 --> 00:19:13.486 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA chuckling]

00:19:13.570 --> 00:19:15.113 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI grunts]

00:19:18.491 --> 00:19:19.784 position:50% align:center
[IKETERU]
Hm? Heh...

00:19:19.868 --> 00:19:23.121 position:50% align:center
Quit looking at-- Ha-ha!

00:19:23.204 --> 00:19:27.500 position:50% align:center
No, no, no, why?
Why play the song now?

00:19:27.584 --> 00:19:31.004 position:50% align:center
You're wearing that and making
that face and I'm dying!

00:19:31.087 --> 00:19:34.257 position:50% align:center
Oh my God, you're
doing it on purpose!

00:19:34.341 --> 00:19:36.426 position:50% align:center
The over-the-shoulder
catwalk death glare!

00:19:36.509 --> 00:19:41.473 position:50% align:center
[UTANO, IKETERU laughing]

00:19:41.556 --> 00:19:43.141 position:50% align:center
[AMON]
It's beautiful.

00:19:43.224 --> 00:19:46.603 position:50% align:center
This is the moment my entire
career has been building up to!

00:19:46.686 --> 00:19:48.897 position:50% align:center
Bravissimo!

00:19:50.565 --> 00:19:51.983 position:50% align:center
[IKETERU]
Bye, everyone!

00:19:52.067 --> 00:19:54.319 position:50% align:center
Yeah, kids. See ya!

00:19:55.904 --> 00:19:58.782 position:50% align:center
[YURI]
Bye-bye!

00:19:58.865 --> 00:20:02.660 position:50% align:center
Hey, Mommy. Didn't you think
the Yakumi Shinobi were cool?

00:20:02.744 --> 00:20:04.162 position:50% align:center
They were, Yuri.

00:20:04.245 --> 00:20:05.830 position:50% align:center
But throw too many
<i>yakumi</i> together,

00:20:05.914 --> 00:20:08.083 position:50% align:center
and their distinctive flavors
crowd each other out.

00:20:08.166 --> 00:20:11.211 position:50% align:center
They really are the ninjas
of Japanese cuisine!

00:20:11.294 --> 00:20:12.545 position:50% align:center
[YURI]
Mh-hm!

00:20:12.629 --> 00:20:16.466 position:50% align:center
Now, wanna go pick up some
groceries with Mommy?

00:20:19.678 --> 00:20:24.015 position:50% align:center
[YURI] Hey, Mommy, at the store,
can we get some shiso?

00:20:24.099 --> 00:20:26.226 position:50% align:center
Aww. Well, we could,

00:20:26.309 --> 00:20:28.353 position:50% align:center
but it might be more
bitter than you think.

00:20:28.436 --> 00:20:29.688 position:50% align:center
It's okay!

00:20:29.771 --> 00:20:32.190 position:50% align:center
Next to the bitterness of
knowing you were on TV

00:20:32.273 --> 00:20:34.150 position:50% align:center
in an outfit that started
with cutoff jorts

00:20:34.234 --> 00:20:36.027 position:50% align:center
and went straight
downhill from there.

00:20:36.111 --> 00:20:39.072 position:50% align:center
How bad could some
old leaf taste?

00:22:20.298 --> 00:22:23.009 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Ready or not, here we come-- Ow!

00:22:23.093 --> 00:22:27.013 position:50% align:center
Seriously. Every friggin' time.

00:22:27.097 --> 00:22:28.723 position:50% align:center
Huh? Holy crap!

00:22:28.807 --> 00:22:30.975 position:50% align:center
Jeez, Uramichi, aren't you
supposed to grow that stuff

00:22:31.059 --> 00:22:32.352 position:50% align:center
in your closet or something?

00:22:32.435 --> 00:22:34.729 position:50% align:center
Wow, real cutting-edge material.

00:22:34.813 --> 00:22:36.731 position:50% align:center
Gonna make shiso gyoza?

00:22:36.815 --> 00:22:39.109 position:50% align:center
How'd you guess? Weird.

00:22:41.736 --> 00:22:42.737 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Yo, I didn't think these

00:22:42.821 --> 00:22:45.323 position:50% align:center
were actually gonna
turn out good!

00:22:45.407 --> 00:22:49.285 position:50% align:center
There is no better combination
than gyoza and beer!

00:22:52.122 --> 00:22:53.748 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Shiso is awesome!

00:22:53.832 --> 00:22:57.002 position:50% align:center
Hey, you think <i>myoga</i>
would go with gyoza?

00:22:57.085 --> 00:22:59.004 position:50% align:center
Wanna know how I know
you made this one?

00:22:59.087 --> 00:23:00.505 position:50% align:center
'Cause the filling's oozing out.

00:23:00.588 --> 00:23:02.882 position:50% align:center
You were about to bite
the thing in half!

00:23:02.966 --> 00:23:04.551 position:50% align:center
Jeez, it's all
gonna get mixed up

00:23:04.634 --> 00:23:07.262 position:50% align:center
in your stomach anyway,
right, Uramichi?

00:23:07.345 --> 00:23:09.014 position:50% align:center
Wha--? Sure.

00:23:09.097 --> 00:23:11.391 position:50% align:center
Uramichi agrees,
so that's two to one!

00:23:11.474 --> 00:23:14.477 position:50% align:center
Hey, remember that
Yakumi Shinobi segment?

00:23:14.561 --> 00:23:16.187 position:50% align:center
I think it aired today.

00:23:16.271 --> 00:23:17.647 position:50% align:center
Yeah.

00:23:17.731 --> 00:23:20.316 position:50% align:center
Hopefully it tanked and we
can forget it ever happened.

00:23:20.400 --> 00:23:21.651 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI] Amon kept
saying he thought it was

00:23:21.735 --> 00:23:23.862 position:50% align:center
a really solid piece
of work, though.

00:23:23.945 --> 00:23:26.781 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Solid waste, more like!

00:23:26.865 --> 00:23:28.283 position:50% align:center
Still, I didn't know
what to expect

00:23:28.366 --> 00:23:30.285 position:50% align:center
when he called us in
after the taping.

00:23:30.368 --> 00:23:32.162 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI] I figured you were
in trouble for something.

00:23:32.245 --> 00:23:34.497 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Of course not! Why would I be?

00:23:34.581 --> 00:23:37.709 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
I think I might hate shiso now.

00:23:41.796 --> 00:23:43.256 position:50% align:center
[GOD]
The Yakumi Shinobi sketch,

00:23:43.340 --> 00:23:46.468 position:50% align:center
in spite of Uramichi's hopes,
and all good sense,

00:23:46.551 --> 00:23:49.512 position:50% align:center
did not flop, but, indeed,
became an instant hit,

00:23:49.596 --> 00:23:53.350 position:50% align:center
quickly earning a place among
the show's recurring segments.